</div>
<div class="comment" id="comment-47744675">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/rmonvfer">rmonvfer</a> 2 days ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">As a Spaniard, this also happens to me. You can either use a VPN or just switch DNS servers to one that doesn’t have anycast nodes in Spain.<p>Cloudflare’s authoritative DNS uses EDNS Client Subnet (ECS) to return different IP pools based on where the query originates. Spanish resolvers get IPs from a range that La Liga blocks. If your recursive resolver is physically outside Spain (or you use DoH&#x2F;DoT to tunnel to one), Cloudflare returns a different, unblocked pool.<p>AdGuard DNS works well for this.</div>
  
  <div class="replies-container" id="replies-47744675"></div>
</div>
